{
  "doc_id": "28992",
  "text": "On the destructive side, various attacks have been demonstrated that undermine the security guarantees of Bitcoin. In eclipse attacks [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] , an adversary exploits the topology of the Bitcoin network to interrupt, or at least delay, the delivery of announcements of new transactions and blocks to a victim node. More expensive \"51%\" attacks, in which the adversary controls more than half of the collective hashing power of the network, allow the adversary to fork the blockchain, and it has been demonstrated [CITATION_4] that such attacks can in fact be carried out with far less than 51% of the hashing power.",
